body:
# Bug report

It seems `experiments.importAsync` does mark the module as async and wraps it in an async function, but doesn't actually await the imported async modules. However, it _does_ work as intended if using the non-standard `import await` syntax, awaiting the async imports in parallel with a Promise.all call.

I realize there has already been a discussion about this in #9177, but my impression was that the `importAsync` flag would enable the standard behavior and always await all async modules, [as defined by the spec](https://github.com/tc39/proposal-top-level-await).

webpack version:  5.0.0-beta.11
Node.js version: 13.5
Operating System: macOS 10.15.2

**What is the current behavior?**

Input:
```js
// index.js
import { add } from './test.js';
import { add as add2 } from './test2.js';

console.log(add(1) + add2(1));
```
```js
// test.js
const a = await Promise.resolve(10);

export function add(b) {
  return a + b;
}
```


Output:
```js
/***/ "./src/index.js":
/*!**********************!*\
  !*** ./src/index.js ***!
  \**********************/
/*! namespace exports */
/*! exports [not provided] [no usage info] */
/*! runtime requirements: __webpack_require__, __webpack_require__.r, __webpack_exports__, module, __webpack_require__.* */
/***/ ((__webpack_module__, __webpack_exports__, __webpack_require__) => {

"use strict";
__webpack_module__.exports = (async () => {
__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);
/* harmony import */ var _test_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__ = __webpack_require__(/*! ./test.js */ "./src/test.js");
/* harmony import */ var _test2_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__ = __webpack_require__(/*! ./test2.js */ "./src/test2.js");



console.log((0,_test_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__.add)(1) + (0,_test2_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__.add)(1));

return __webpack_exports__;
})();

/***/ }),
```

**What is the expected behavior?**

Output: (using import await)
```js
/***/ "./src/index.js":
/*!**********************!*\
  !*** ./src/index.js ***!
  \**********************/
/*! namespace exports */
/*! exports [not provided] [no usage info] */
/*! runtime requirements: __webpack_require__, __webpack_require__.r, __webpack_exports__, module, __webpack_require__.* */
/***/ ((__webpack_module__, __webpack_exports__, __webpack_require__) => {

"use strict";
__webpack_module__.exports = (async () => {
__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);
/* harmony import */ var _test_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__ = __webpack_require__(/*! ./test.js */ "./src/test.js");
/* harmony import */ var _test2_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__ = __webpack_require__(/*! ./test2.js */ "./src/test2.js");
([_test2_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__, _test_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__] = await Promise.all([_test2_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__, _test_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__]));



console.log((0,_test_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__.add)(1) + (0,_test2_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__.add)(1));

return __webpack_exports__;
})();

/***/ }),
```
